cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with a differentiable softmax operator for reinforcement learning. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as reinforcement learning is often used in robotics. It could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with sequential decision making. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the new operator introduced in the paper is a neural network-based approach.
